<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911009-0131</DOCNO><DOCID>911009-0131.</DOCID><HL>   Ohio Edison Co.</HL><DATE>10/09/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A16</SO><CO>   MRN OEC</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)UTILITIES (UTI)</MS><IN>HEAVY CONSTRUCTION; INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL (CON)ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)</IN><RE>IDAHO (ID)NORTH AMERICA (NME)OHIO (OH)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   AKRON, Ohio -- Ohio Edison Co. said it will lease at least200 megawatts of electric generating capacity from a plantthat Summit Energy Storage Inc. plans to build.   The proposed plant would generate power by releasing waterstored in a reservoir through a mine shaft to turbines abouthalf a mile underground. The water would be collected andpumped back to the reservoir during the night, when there'sless demand for energy. Morrison Knudsen Corp., a Boise,Idaho, construction concern, is designing and building the$1.7 billion plant.</LP><TEXT>   Construction of the 1,500 megawatt plant is expected tobegin no later than April 1995, with the first 250-megawattgenerating unit to be completed as early as 1998. Ohio Edisonwon't spend any money on the facility until it's operational.</TEXT></DOC>